<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENING Q &amp; A: LEAF CURL ON TOMATO PLANT CAUSED BY COLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Bill Sidnam 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Q: What is causing the lower leaves of my tomato plant to curl? The rest of the 
plant is fine. 
</P>
<P>
A: Don't worry. This condition is caused by a cold spell early in the plant's 
growth cycle. It will not affect new growth and the plant should grow normally 
and produce fruit. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Sidnam 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
