</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Page 58; Calendar Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
89 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUETS WITH SPANISH GUITAR. Laurindo Almeida, guitar; Salli Terri, mezzo; Martin 
Ruderman, flute. 
</P>
<P>
EMI CDM-7 63256 2 (compact disc). This elegant, re-released collection of 20 
miniatures mixes predictable selections from Ibert, Villa-Lobos, Ravel and 
Falla with lesser-known gems, particularly from the Brazilian composers Jayme 
Ovalle, Valdemar Henrique, Ernani Braga and Francisco Mignone. Easy-listening 
in the best sense, but the remastered sonics sound even more glossily 
reverberant than on the original vinyl. JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Recording Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
