ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY MANGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEETHOVEN: SYMPHONIES NOS. 7 &amp; 8. Chicago Symphony conducted by Sir Georg 
Solti. 
</P>
<P>
London 425 525-2. No surprises here -- the performers are too familiar to us 
and to each other, and Solti too straightforward a conductor. Neither of these 
performances catch fire with the kind of emotional abandon and rhythmic 
vivacity others have found. But they're nevertheless surprisingly attractive in 
their plain-spoken sturdiness, effective despite (or because?) of the steady 
sobriety of their unfolding. Underlying the apparent effortlessness of the 
playing, however, is a firm hand at the helm, and an unselfish intellect that 
knows this music doesn't require much prodding to work. TIMOTHY MANGAN 
</P>
