<P>
EAGLES NEST EGGS: As we predicted earlier this year, the Eagles have gotten 
back together and are working on a greatest-hits package. In fact, original 
members Don Henley, Joe Walsh, Timothy B. Schmit and Don Felder have been in a 
Los Angeles studio recording several new songs for possible inclusion on the 
album. 
</P>
<P>
Who's missing from that list? None other than Glenn Frey, who didn't show up 
for the recent sessions. Has Frey had another falling out with Henley? Can the 
band pull off its much-anticipated 1991 reunion tour without Frey on board? 
Stay tuned. The band is scheduled to have another recording session in 
mid-December. Insiders say if Frey doesn't make an appearance, it could spell 
trouble for any reunion tour. 
</P>
