<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE LEAF-BLOWER AS MIND-BLOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Minor as my complaint may be, it is nonetheless aggravating. It is the newest 
infernal machine: the leaf-blower! 
</P>
<P>
They are analogous to motorcycles that never move! They just rev and roar until 
everyone within the infernal machine's noise zone is moved but mental 
millimeters away from madness and mayhem. 
</P>
<P>
I realize that brooms are passe, but at least broomsters would, at the end of 
their sweepings, stoop to pick up what they had assembled. The leaf-blowers do 
not remove what is being blown -- they but relocate it! 
</P>
<P>
No doubt these monsters are here to stay but must they be made so powerful 
that, even muffled, they are outrageously offensive? Please support the 
legislation that is offered to tone down this pure pollution device! 
</P>
<P>
DAN DELEHANT, La Habra 
</P>
</TEXT>
