<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLEASE, LEAVE LAGUNA CANYON IN PEACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
History, religion and philosophy have taught that the excessive acquisition of 
wealth is damaging to human happiness. 
</P>
<P>
The citizens of Laguna Beach have demonstrated their appreciation of this 
received wisdom by voting to tax themselves for 20 years to preserve Laguna 
Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
We must convince our elected officials, developers and proponents of the San 
Joaquin freeway of this universal truth. 
</P>
<P>
Housing already built in southern Orange County is not selling. It is appalling 
that such a massive intrusion in our coastal canyons is being contemplated for 
dedicated, but unbuilt housing. 
</P>
<P>
SIEGLINDE JOHNSON, Laguna Beach 
</P>
