<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA WOMEN LOSE OPENER TO IOWA, 81-52 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IOWA CITY, Iowa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tricia Waugh collected 13 points and 13 rebounds to lead Iowa to an 81-52 
victory over UCLA Saturday in the first round of the Amana-Hawkeye women's 
basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
In the other first-round game, Dana Chapman scored 29 points to power Louisiana 
State past Kansas, 74-63. 
</P>
<P>
Misti Chennault scored 22 points for Kansas. 
</P>
<P>
Iowa will play LSU in today's championship game, with UCLA meeting Kansas in 
the third-place game. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Hawkeyes built a 36-24 lead at halftime and then roared away from the 
Bruins with a 13-6 surge to start the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Toni Foster scored 16 points and Cassandra Rahming and Necole Tunsill each 
added 11 for Iowa, which made 56% of its shots in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Rehema Stephens had 14 points for UCLA, Detra Lockhart added 12 and Gen van 
Oosten had 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
