<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAWKS PULL SEVENTH LOSS IN ROW FROM THE JAWS OF VICTORY, 124-121 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN HAFNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With Dominique Wilkins leading the way, it seemed the Hawks would end their 
losing streak Saturday night at Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
There were only 10 1/2 minutes to play and the Atlanta Hawks led the 
Philadelphia 76ers, 106-88. 
</P>
<P>
But three-point field goals by Kenny Payne and Charles Barkley in the final 22 
seconds let the 76ers pull out a 124-121 victory. 
</P>
<P>
After the 76ers pulled to 121-119 with 22 seconds to play on Payne's shot, 
Wilkins, who scored 39 points, was tied up by Hersey Hawkins with 15 seconds 
left. 
</P>
<P>
The 76ers won the tip and Barkley sank a three-point shot with eight seconds to 
play. Rickey Green's two free throws with two seconds to play completed the 
scoring and the Hawks lost their seventh in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Barkley, in early foul trouble, played only 33 minutes and had 23 points and 
seven rebounds. DAN HAFNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
