<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Forward Anja Bordt scored 27 points to lead St. Mary's to an 83-68 victory over 
San Diego State in the championship of the St. Mary's Invitational in Moraga. 
St. Mary's (2-0) jumped out to a 46-23 lead at halftime and never looked back. 
SDSU (1-1) was led by center Kieishsha Garnes, who had a game-high 30 points. 
Garnes and Melanie Usher (10 points) were named to the all-tournament team. 
Bordt was the tournament's most valuable player. 
</P>
