<HEADLINE>
<P>
MATER DEI WILL PLAY QUARTZ HILL AT OCC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Surprising Mater Dei High School won a coin toss and will play host to Quartz 
Hill at 7:30 p.m. Friday at Orange Coast College's LeBard Stadium in the 
semifinals of the Southern Section Division I football playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (7-5) advanced with a 34-20 upset of top-seeded Eisenhower in the 
second round Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon will play host to Loyola at College of the Canyons on Saturday in the 
other semifinal game. 
</P>
<P>
In Division II, Mission Viejo will play host to South Coast League rival 
Capistrano Valley on Friday, and El Toro will meet Paramount Saturday in a 
rematch of last year's Division III title game. Both games begin at 7:30 at 
Mission Viejo High School. The pairings for Orange County teams: 
</P>
<P>
Friday's games 
</P>
<P>
Division I: Quartz Hill (10-2) vs. Mater Dei (7-5) at Orange Coast College; 
Division II: Capistrano Valley (10-2) at Mission Viejo (11-1); Division III: 
Hart (9-3) vs. Esperanza (12-0) at Valencia High School; Division VI: Sunny 
Hills (9-3) at Valencia (11-1); Division IX: Valley Christian (6-5) vs. 
Whittier Christian (11-0) at Whittier College. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's games 
</P>
