<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALTADENA; 
</P>
<P>
CHRISTMAS TREE LANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Volunteers are needed to help string lights on Christmas Tree Lane, Town 
Councilman Gene Coffman said Tuesday. Those interested in volunteering to 
string lights from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday and Dec. 8 may call the Altadena 
Chamber of Commerce at (818) 794-3988, or simply show up. A party to celebrate 
the opening of the lane this season will be held under the deodar trees at 6 
p.m. Dec. 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
