CHILDREN'S SHELTER BACKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Town Council voted Tuesday to support a proposal to create a short-term 
residential shelter for neglected or abused infants and young children. 
</P>
<P>
Lorraine Castro, executive director of the Bienvenidos Children's Center in 
West Covina, told the Town Council that the center, if approved by the county, 
will occupy a former YMCA site at 183 E. Palm St. 
</P>
