<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL; 
</P>
<P>
LAKEWOOD ST. JOSEPH'S DEF. USDHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TERRY RATHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gleen Bermundo had 22 kills to lead St. Joseph's of Lakewood to a 9-15, 15-17, 
16-14, 16-14, 15-13 victory over University of San Diego High School in the 
Southern California girls' volleyball Division II semifinals at USDHS. 
</P>
<P>
St. Joseph's (18-1) battled back from a two game deficit to defeat the Dons. 
</P>
<P>
Heather Hofmans had 37 assists for St. Joseph's. 
</P>
<P>
"It was an exciting match," St. Joseph's Coach Michael Hinton said. "I think 
both teams showed a lot of character. Neither team quit. When I came down here, 
I didn't know what to expect. USDHS is a fine school." 
</P>
<P>
USDHS's Michelle Rico had 37 kills and Rose Dowling had 89 assists in the loss. 
Defensively, Rico had 14 digs and Christina Alvarado had 19. 
</P>
<P>
USDHS led in the third game, 14-10, before Bermundo reeled off several kills to 
seal the match for St. Joseph's. 
</P>
<P>
"We aren't ashamed of how we played out there," Dons Coach Rob Gorney said. "I 
told them that when you set a goal, go ahead and finish it. It seemed we were 
the stronger team and all we had to do was finish it." 
</P>
<P>
The Dons finished the season 22-3. TERRY RATHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
